From Blaine Gardner Subject Re Touring the southwest In article Kim Sharpe writes A few of us are touring Sothwest Utah in mid June to see the Do any of you have some helpful hints on where to stay or things to see do Plans are to see Bryce Zion Is the Grand close at that point or is an additional trip required Well it's closer to Bryce than Bryce is to I'd spend a lot of time studying the maps there's a lot of you can't get there from here in that You might want to hit the Grand Canyon on the way up from California loop around to Canyonlands Moab Arches and then back down towards Bryce Zion on the way Make sure you ride US between Capitol Reef and Bryce it's been on a number of top roads A nice booklet detailing a lot of interesting paved Byways and unpaved Backways roads can be ordered from the Utah Travel I think you can also get a state map from them just for Utah Byways and Backways US Utah Travel Council Council Hall Capitol Hill Salt Lake City UT Blaine Gardner Evans Sutherland